ition of Egypt as "Two Lands"—no longer the lands of Upper and Lower Egypt, but of a shared Greek and Egyptian culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aComparative literaturexEgyptian and Greek. 0aComparative literaturexGreek and Egyptian. 0aEgyptian poetryxHistory and criticismxEgyptxAlexandria. 0aEgyptian poetryzEgyptzAlexandriaxHistory and criticism. 0aGreek poetry, HellenisticxHistory and criticismxEgyptxAlexandria. 0aGreek poetry, HellenisticzEgyptzAlexandriaxHistory and criticism. 0aLanguage and culturexEgyptxAlexandria. 0aLanguage and culturezEgyptzAlexandria. 0aPoeticsxHistoryxTo 500. 0aPoeticsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPoeticsxHistoryyTo 500. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aalexandrian court.  aalexandrian poetry.  aalexandrian poets.  aancient egypt.  aancient greece.  aapollonius.  aargonautica.  acallimachus.  aegypt.  aegyptian culture.  aegyptian history.  aegyptian people.  aegyptian poetry.  agreek poetry.  ahelen.  ahellenism.  aheracles.  ahiero of syracuse.  ahymns.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary theory.  amythology.  anonfiction.  apharoah.  apoetics.  apoetry.  apolitical values.  aptolemaic court.  aptolemies.  aptolemy philadelphus.  aregencies.  aroyalty.  arulers.  atheocritus.  atheogonies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092738440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927384/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles